Sometimes it's the simplest of combinations that are the most satisfying. This hearty barley salad is full of crunchy cucumber, juicy tomatoes, and creamy avocado. A touch of olive oil and balsamic are all it needs to shine. Perfectly seasoned, perfectly seared chicken seals the deal.

== Barley ==

Wash and dry all produce. Remove the @chicken breasts{12%ounce} from the refrigerator and bring to room temperature. Place the @pearl barley{3/4%cup} and a large pinch of @salt{pinch} in a #small pot{} with enough water to cover by 2 inches. Bring to a boil and cook for ~{25-30%minutes}, until tender. Drain.

Core, seed, and cube the @roma tomato{1}(cored, seeded, and cubed). Thinly slice the @scallions{2}, keeping the greens and whites separate. Peel the @cucumber{1}(peeled), then cut into ½-inch cubes. Halve, pit, and peel the @avocado{1}(halved, pitted, and peeled), then cut into small cubes.

== Salad ==

Toss the tomato, cucumber, scallion whites, and avocado cubes into a #large bowl{} with @balsamic vinegar{1%tablespoon}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

== Chicken ==

With about 15 minutes left on the barley, heat a drizzle of @olive oil{} in a #large pan{} over medium heat. Pat dry the chicken with a #paper towel{}. Season on all sides with @salt{}, @pepper{}, and @paprika{1%teaspoon}. Add the chicken to the pan and cook for ~{5-6%minutes} per side, until cooked through. Let rest for ~{5%minutes} before thinly slicing.

Toss the barley into the #bowl{} with the vegetables along with a large drizzle of @olive oil{1%tablespoon} and more @balsamic vinegar{1%tablespoon}, if desired. Season to taste with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

== To Serve ==

Serve the paprika-rubbed chicken on a bed of barley, tomato, and avocado salad. Garnish with the reserved scallion greens. Enjoy!